text: help for wherever you are on your github journey. at the heart of github is an open-source version control system (vcs) called git. git is responsible for everything github-related that happens locally on your computer. you can connect to github using the secure shell protocol (ssh), which provides a secure channel over an unsecured network. you can create a repository on github to store and collaborate on your project's files, then manage the repository's name and location. create sophisticated
